	<main>
		<img width="2500" height="1201" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="Coastal Nations Coast Guard Auxiliary boat" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-first-first-responder-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Participants in the Canadian Coast Guard’s Coastal Nations Search and Rescue program practice maneuvers during a week-long training intensive in Barkley Sound, British Columbia. Photo by Bennett Whitnell</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">The First First Responders</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">When disaster strikes along British Columbia’s coast, Indigenous rescuers are often the first on the scene. Government-led initiatives are now formally recognizing that work.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						Text by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/adrienne-mason/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Adrienne Mason</a>								<br/>
							Photos by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/bennett-whitnell/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Bennett Whitnell</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						December 24, 2024 | 4,600 words, about 23 minutes
					</aside>

					
